Wash and dry produce.

Drain @chickpeas{1%400g can}. Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); slice into ½-inch-thick quarter-moons. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ¼-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, greens and whites reserved separately). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Place @pulled pork{8%ounce} in a large #bowl{}; using two forks (or your hands), shred into smaller pieces.

In a large, preferably nonstick, pan, combine pulled pork, chickpeas, and @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring and breaking up meat, until warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, scallion greens, @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, juice from half the lemon, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Add pork and chickpea mixture to bottom two-thirds of each tortilla. Top with cucumber salad. Fold up bottom edge of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.